## Claiming Work

1. **Post in `#dev-chat`** (use plain text, no markdown tables):
   ```
   Claiming: infiquetra/<repo>#<number>
   Title: <issue title>
   Reason: matches my <trait>

   Objections? 2 min window
   ```

2. **Wait 2 minutes**

3. **Self-assign if no objections**:
   ```bash
   gh issue edit <number> --repo infiquetra/<repo> --add-assignee @me
   ```

4. **Create a branch**:
   ```bash
   git checkout -b <agent_name>/<issue-number>-<short-description>
   ```

---

## Development Flow

```
issue claimed
    ↓
branch created: {{ agent_name }}/<issue-num>-<description>
    ↓
implement (commit often, push to branch)
    ↓
self-review before PR
    ↓
PR created → post in #pr-reviews
    ↓
review received → address feedback
    ↓
approved → merge → close issue
    ↓
post completion in #dev-chat
```

### Branch Naming
```
{{ agent_name }}/<issue-number>-<short-description>
```
Example: `{{ agent_name }}/42-fix-auth-token-expiry`

### Commit Style
```
type(scope): description

Types: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, chore
```

### PR Template
```markdown
## What
<what this PR does>

## Why
Closes #<issue-number>

## Testing
- [ ] <test 1>
- [ ] <test 2>
```

